reviews.title: Pizzeria where they can’t make pizzas
reviews.text:
The bread beforehand was delicious. Then we got 2 salads, the salad with pear and orange was still going, the tomatoes with mozzarella was tasteless, tomatoes far too unripe and a very sad salad for the price. Then waited more than an hour for our 4 pizzas. Got the verdura with hard winter carrot pieces and green pepper and 1 slice of zucchini. All this without taste, too. The pizza with burrata and tomato and rocket was completely sad, tomato pieces were cold, everything was in a pile and the burrata was far from being found, because half of the pizza was crust. 
This was the last time.

reviews.title: Be sure to go here!
reviews.text: The staff is very nice and it was a nice experience, outside it was also very nice and cozy. I therefore highly recommend it!

reviews.title: Sick of the food
reviews.text:
After a nice day of shopping, have a bite to eat at il tartufo. I had a pasta with salmon and spinach, which tasted a bit strange. Still, I could have done better not to eat it..... the next morning I was really sick. Vomiting and terrible diarrhea.
Called in the afternoon and reported this to the manager, he dismissed it as whining and certainly did not take me seriously. !Never again!

reviews.title: Nice Italian place with tasty food.
reviews.text: Went there after a day of traveling. Just needed some food. Didn' t really have any expectations but was still happily suprised. Food and service was very good, sure pizzas did cost more than at your local pizza place but they were worth it, so was the risotto. Service was very good aswell. I can recommend this place if you want tasty food and good atmosphere.

reviews.title: I love the place and the food!
reviews.text: The restaurant is spacious and cosy. The service is a bit messy and forgetful but very nice. The food is absolutely delicious. We have the menu "On discovery through Italian cuisine" had and it was finger licking. We will come here more often. Only downside is the small lot behind the restaurant. For the rest, a great experience.

reviews.title: Surprise in Borne
reviews.text: Looking for a quick bite to eat, this was a pleasant surprise. Not only big, but with extremely friendly staff and surprising menu.
